{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017skzry8pBioDiPhEKgV2pP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The headless service has no endpoints. That's the problem - the pods aren't yet ready, so they're not being added to the endpoints. With a headless service, DNS entries are added based on the pod IPs when they are \"ready\" (or always if `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` is set).\n\nFor CockroachDB to form a cluster, the pods need to be able to resolve each other even before they're ready. The fix is to set `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service.\n\nThis is a common fix for CockroachDB clusters - without it, the pods can't resolve each other's DNS names until they're ready, but they can't become ready until they can resolve each other.\nNow I need to update the headless service to include that flag so the pods can discover each other during initialization.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":458,"cache_read_input_tokens":36658,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":458},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f97a740c-324d-49d3-94dc-b8172479a1b6","uuid":"8804c017-1fe7-49e1-8883-3e04aee84f7d","request_id":"req_011Cc9Xd5GU9gn46qd8Eg2xk"}
